HEADWORD: Endoskeleton
<hw>En`do*skel"e*ton</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Endo-</ets> + <ets>skeleton</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>The bony, cartilaginous, or other internal framework of an animal,
as distinguished from the <contr>exoskeleton</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

